items.title: Israeli military says first stages of assault on Gaza City have begun
items.description: Call-up letters have gone out to 60,000 reservists to bolster an operation which is expected to last until next year.

items.title: Israel approves controversial West Bank settlement project
items.description: The Palestinian Authority says the decision is illegal and will "destroy" the prospects for a two-state solution.

items.title: Watch: JD Vance heckled as he meets National Guard in Washington DC
items.description: Protesters shouted at Vance, Pete Hegseth and Stephen Miller as they entered DC's largest rail hub.

items.title: Fire still burning in one of world's tallest trees after three days
items.description: With about 50 ft already lost, the fire may impact the Doerner Fir's standing in global height rankings, officials say.

items.title: Why Donetsk matters so much for Ukraine's defences
items.description: For Ukraine to lose western Donetsk would mean the fall of a bulwark against any future Russian advance.
